Number buttons:
1. At the start and after an operation if you press a number, the previous one disapears. (CHECK)
2. After an operator is pressed, pressing a number only shows the new number.
Operator buttons:
1. Pressing an operator button, highlights it, and it is not shown on the entry
2. If there is already an operator present, pressing another operator changes the current operator to the last one. (CHECK)
Equals button:
1. Pressing the equal button shows the result of the operation. Pressing it more than once repeats the operation to the result of each operation.
Comma button:
1. If there is already a comma in the shown number, you cannot have another one. (CHECK)